Crew certification procedures (an annual requirement) pretty much
insured that folks were ready to go and fully qualified to do so. It
was a formal briefing by a crew of a nuclear target line with detailed
descriptions of procedures, weapon, route, delivery, safeguards, etc.
Typically a pretty high pressure time for crews who were going to get
a chance to meet the wing commander or deputy/operations up-close and
personal.

